title: Great news today between my favorite sports these days: nose blowing and coughing... Results from Java blood test are good: she is stable with the pills dosage she has now even if she doesn't like taking them. Thyroid and kidney are good, so we will do the tests every year instead of every six months now (she doesn't like this either - they have to shave her neck). Still being vigilant about the potential symptoms of hyperthyroidism (lack of appetite and weight loss mostly), but she's fine for now! It's common with older cats... I like talking with people brighter and more successful than me, learn from them and take action to always be a better version of myself. On the other side, I'm less into life coaches, but after I watched the Netflix documentary about Tony Robbins, I was in. I wanted to see, to try, to experience the journey. It's a leap of faith, a test for me. I don't know if I'll like it, neither if it will be life changing as much as it is for everyone I've read about, but without trying, I won't know.
